The paper deals with testing and learning probability distributions, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of oracles to access the unknown distribution is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM), which are also relevant sub-categories.
